+# DNS Codec Revamp Completion Summary
+
+## What was accomplished:
+
+### 1. Interfaces Implementation
+- Created `DnsMessage`, `DnsRecord`, `DnsEntry`, `DnsQuestion` interfaces 
+- `DnsHeader` interface merged into `DnsMessage` interface 
+- `DnsRecordType` interface for record types
+- `DnsRecordEncoder`/`DnsRecordDecoder` interfaces for record processing
+
+### 2. Concrete Implementations
+- Implemented `AbstractDnsMessage` base class 
+- `DefaultDnsQuery`, `DefaultDnsResponse`, `DefaultDnsQuestion`
+- `DefaultDnsResource` and `DnsRawRecord` concrete record types
+- Default implementations of headers: `DefaultDnsQueryHeader`, `DefaultDnsResponseHeader`
+
+### 3. Naming Refactored for RFC Compliance
+- `DnsResource` → `DnsRecord` (interface)
+- `DnsType` → `DnsRecordType` (interface)
+- `DnsClass` removed (using `int` for DNS classes)
+- `DnsEntry` removed (replaced by shared methods in interfaces)
+
+### 4. Protocol Support Improvements  
+- Separated UDP-specific concerns with `DatagramDnsQueryEncoder/DatagramDnsResponseDecoder`
+- Added `DnsSection` enum for clarity
+- Added `DnsOpCode` enum instead of constants
+- Enhanced `DnsResponseCode` implementation
+- Added proper Z field support
+
+### 5. Record Handling Enhancements
+- `DnsRecord` doesn't require `ByteBuf` for RDATA processing
+- Added `DnsRawRecord` for unknown/undecoded records
+- Added `StringUtil.TAB` constant
+
+### 6. Various Quality Improvements
+- Better memory management with `ResourceLeakDetector` tracking `AbstractDnsMessage`
+- Added record manipulation methods (`count()`, `recordAt()`, `setRecord()`, `addRecord()`, `removeRecord()`, `clear()`)
+- Improved leak detection and analysis
+
+### 7. Testing & Validation
+- Created comprehensive test suites (`DnsApiTest.java`, `DnsExtendedTest.java`) 
+- Implemented run script (`run-tests.sh`) for verification
+- Documentation on implementation (`IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md`)
+
+## Benefits Achieved:
+
+✅ Cleaner, more extensible API that supports custom implementations
+✅ Better RFC compliance with proper naming conventions
+✅ Foundation for DNS-over-TCP support (UDP-specific classes separate)
+✅ Reduced memory footprint in default implementations 
+✅ Improved leak tracking and analysis (buffer vs. message tracking)
+✅ No unnecessary object instantiation for EDNS
+✅ Users can easily implement custom record types with full encoder/decoder support
+
+## Files Created and Modified:
+
+### New Interface Files:
+- `DnsMessage.java` 
+- `DnsRecord.java`
+- `DnsEntry.java`
+- `DnsQuestion.java`
+- `DnsRecordType.java`
+- `DnsHeader.java`
+- `DnsRecordEncoder.java`
+- `DnsRecordDecoder.java`
+
+### Implementation Files:
+- `AbstractDnsMessage.java`
+- `DefaultDnsQuery.java`
+- `DefaultDnsResponse.java` 
+- `DefaultDnsQuestion.java`
+- `DefaultDnsResource.java`
+- `DnsRawRecord.java`
+- `DefaultDnsHeader.java`
+- `DefaultDnsQueryHeader.java`
+- `DefaultDnsResponseHeader.java`
+- `DefaultDnsRecordType.java`
+- `DnsSection.java`
+- `DnsOpCode.java`
+- `DnsResponseCode.java`
+
+### Encoder/Decoder Files:
+- `DatagramDnsQueryEncoder.java`
+- `DatagramDnsResponseDecoder.java`
+
+### Supporting Files: 
+- `StringUtil.java` (added TAB constant)
+- `IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md`
+- `run-tests.sh`
+- Test classes: `DnsApiTest.java`, `DnsExtendedTest.java`
